This is an example of how you can set the placeholder text within a form to size proprotionately to it. 

You can change the font size value to suit. Ie 4vh or 2 vh et.
Line height nicely separates the boxes vertically 

.contact-form {flex-grow:1; flex-basis:33.3%; line-height:53px; }


input {height:43px; width:280px; }

input::placeholder {font-size:3vh;}
input {font-size:3vh;}


